{
  "texts": [
    "To this end, it appears to us that the lack of reproducibility related to LLMs is similar to that of other tools-the results should be replicable but the precise process that went into deciding how to create those specific results may not be.",
    "In our opinion, that is simply how the creative process of science works.",
    "More generally, we also caution that all uses of LLMs and AI require careful consideration of credit and liability.",
    "These considerations are relevant both in terms of intellectual contribution (i.e., who came up with the relevant ideas), and intellectual property (i.e., who has copyrighted the material that you or your LLM are using).",
    "Both the United States and the EU are in the midst of enacting regulations on the topic, and, in most cases, it appears that, if an LLM draws heavily on copyrighted text or images in the production of a published output, the human author may be held liable for copyright infringement."
  ]
}